Pertech 6100 Driver Readme

This product will work for Linux Ubuntu. Other distributions can work if you edit the install.sh file accordingly.

Install Instructions

Extract the contents of the compressed file to any location of your choosing.
Open up the Terminal and navigate to the location of the extracted files. You should see the install.sh file in this directory
Run the install.sh file

sudo ./install.sh

Make sure you have the right permissions.
Wait for the installation process to complete.
Once complete, navigate to the 6100-C-Test folder.
Plug in the 6100 Check Scanner
run the gtktest executable

sudo ./gtktest

The program should start up. Press the Connect button to make sure the driver works properly.

If you have any questions, please contact support by calling 1-800-800-6614 Monday-Friday 8am-5pm



